Vice President Kamala Harris delivered a speech at Southfield High School for the Arts and Technology in Southfield, Michigan. She commended the young leaders in attendance, highlighting their resilience and generosity. Harris discussed various issues, such as mental health, college affordability, climate change, gun violence, and reproductive rights. She called on the young leaders to use their voices, register to vote, and continue to advocate for change. Harris emphasized the importance of young people's involvement in shaping the future of the nation.